"(1)  \nShadows stretched along the emerald-green grass of the course, where the air hummed with an unspoken energy. Through the low-hanging mist, Zoe’s boots pressed against the dew-laden ground, her gaze fixed on the fluttering banners strung above the grand entrance. It was a night when moonlight seemed to have woven itself into the architecture, silver threads tracing the curves of the black course’s stone outcrops and the restless trees. Around her, murmurs of anticipation rose and faded like the shifting lights on a wizard’s staff.\n\n(2)  \nA velvet rope parted before her, revealing rows of illuminated stands. Framed in amber glass, photographs hovered in mid-air—a dance of light and shadow that drew Zoe’s breath. She moved through the crowd slowly, shoulders tense from nerves that had nothing to do with the weather but everything to do with the purpose of this gathering. Faces twisted in admiration or disbelief; some visitors leaned in, whispering theories, while others lingered motionless, as if afraid to move and disturb the spell.\n\n(3)  \nA tall, robed figure with obsidian eyes beckoned her forward, gesturing to a display that seemed to shimmer faintly. Behind the translucent barrier, images swirled in a sequence that shifted when viewed from different angles. Zoe caught glimpses of ordinary landscapes rendered extraordinary—mountains glowing with inner fire, rivers that shimmered like liquid topaz, and faces half-lit by an ethereal, cobalt glow. The artistry was as much alchemy as craft, and she felt the pulse of magic in every frame.\n\n(4)  \nShe noticed two other guests nearby. One, a thin man in silver-lacquered armor, leaned forward, his breath fogging in the chilly air as he scrutinized a portrait of an unfamiliar figure bathed in unnatural hues. The woman beside him wore a cloak embroidered with tiny, moving sprites. Their conversations, hushed and intense, drifted on syllables she couldn’t quite decipher—words that might have been spells, or simply the language of those who truly understood the art on display.\n\n(5)  \nTonight, November 13, 2026, at Bethpage Black Course, Zoe Brown found herself at the center of the gathering as the guest of honor. A small podium stood at the heart of the exhibition, flanked by photographs that seemed to pulse with the memory of their subjects’ joys and sorrows. The event had been named in her honor—a"